<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1001,1170]" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,377,1001,1026]" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">Appearance in life</emphasis>
is often quite distinctive, with some or all of the elongate second-instar females / exuviae containing pupillarial adult females having a median series of red-brown spots or transverse red-brown stripes on a yellow background (
<figureCitation box="[382,449,1073,1098]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1892,1914]" captionTargetBox="[217,1369,1225,1868]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[217,1369,1225,1868]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Fiorinia phantasma appearance in life: (A) females and immature male scales (white) on Calophyllum neoebudicum leaf in American Samoa, 21. x. 2008; (B) adult females inside second-instar exuviae with some pigmented banding; (C) adult female inside second-instar exuviae with well-developed pigmented banding (photographs by M. Schmaedick); (D) adult female inside second instar exuviae with no pigmented banding on Arundinaria sp., U. K. (© Fera)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/244849/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">
Fig. 
<number box="[435,449,1074,1098]" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Garcia" box="[504,645,1073,1098]" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" refString="Garcia, J. N. (2011) Fiorinia phantasma Cockerell and Robinson (Hemiptera: Diaspididae), an armored scale pest new to Hawaii. Proceedings of the Hawaiian Entomological Society, 43, 59 - 61. Available from: http: // scholarspace. manoa. hawaii. edu / bitstream / handle / 10125 / 21682 / 43 _ 59 - 61. pdf? sequence = 1 (accessed 24 May 2015)" type="journal article" year="2011">
Garcia 
<number box="[586,645,1074,1098]" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" value="2011.0">2011</number>
</bibRefCitation>
); however, sometimes there may be no striped individuals present in a colony. 
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:33433" box="[239,320,1110,1134]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:33433" name="Hawaii Department of Agriculture" pageId="4" pageNumber="295">HDOA</collectionCode>
(
<number box="[336,396,1110,1134]" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" value="2011.0">2011</number>
), Anon. (
<number box="[499,558,1110,1134]" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" value="2012.0">2012</number>
) and 
<bibRefCitation author="Bethke" box="[621,782,1109,1134]" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" refString="Bethke, J. A. (2012) Insect hot topics: new scale insect in Hawaii. UCNFA News. University of California, Division of Agriculture and Natural Sciences. Available from: http: // ucanr. edu / sites / UCNFAnews / Insect _ Hot _ Topics / INSECT _ HOT _ TOPICS __ New _ scale _ insect _ in _ Hawaii / (accessed 14 July 2015)" type="journal article" year="2012">
Bethke (
<number box="[715,774,1110,1134]" pageId="4" pageNumber="295" value="2012.0">2012</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
mention a colour form that is entirely red, but this has not been present in the samples studied by GW.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
